        "sender_full_name": "Rémy Degenne",
        "timestamp": 1729177862
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Whoops sorry, should be Kalle in the header. James didn't have anything to do with this specific definition</p>",
        "id": 477467319,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1729177913
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"350992\">Rémy Degenne</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/144837-PR-reviews/topic/.2317859.20feat.3A.20consistent.20family.20of.20kernels/near/477467104\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>That PR contains a definition but no lemmas about it. Are there no basic facts about it in your project that would go to that same file?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is definitely fair. Maybe we should at least prove that regular conditional kernels of a filtration satisfy this consistency. For Gibbs measures, the logic goes the other way, however: this notion of consistency is a part of the definition (of a Gibbsian specification, which is used to define Gibbs measures). In the project we also did not yet reach the results about Gibbs measures we aimed for. Sorry, I have not had Lean time for some months, but Yaël has been getting some parts of the project PR'd.</p>",
        "id": 477469141,
        "sender_full_name": "Kalle Kytölä",
        "timestamp": 1729178427
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(hopefully all of it, so that other people can build on it by formalising the juicy Chapter 2 !)</p>",
